<%args>
$annotation_helper
</%args>

<div id="ferret">

<form id="ferret-form" action="" method="post">
  <input type="hidden" id="ferret-term-id"/>
  <textarea id="ferret-term-entry" name="ferret-term-entry"
            type="textarea" cols="30" rows="4"
            placeholder="start typing ..."
            disabled="true"></textarea>
  <div id="ferret-term-children" style="display: none">
GO annotations should always be made to the most specific term possible.
These are the child terms of the term you have chosen.
In this instance would any of the children be more appropriate for the
experiment you are curating?
    <div id="ferret-term-children-list">
    </div>
  </div>
  <div id="ferret-term-details" style="display: none">
    <div>
      <span class="term-id" id="ferret-term-id-display"></span>
    has definition: <div id="ferret-term-definition" class="term-definition"></div>
    </div>
    <div id="ferret-confirm">
      <input id="ferret-reset-button" name="reset" type="reset" value="Search again" class="button" />
      <input id="ferret-previous-button" name="previous" type="submit" value="Previous term" class="button"
             style="display: none"/>
      or
      <input name="confirm-def" type="submit" value="Confirm definition" class="button" />
    </div>
  </div>
</form>
</div>
